   "source": [
    "## Extra Question (5 Points)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Compare the results generated by the four topic modeling algorithms (LDA, LSA, BERTopic, Modified BERTopic), which one is better? You should explain the reasons in details.**\n",
    "\n",
    "**This question will compensate for any points deducted in this exercise. Maximum marks for the exercise is 100 points.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "uIjnKSs8vB_p"
   },
   "source": [
    "In this assignment, four topic modeling techniques were applied: Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA), Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA), BERTopic, and Modified BERTopic. Each method has its own strengths and limitations in terms of topic quality, coherence, and interpretability.\n",
    "1. LDA (Latent Dirichlet Allocation)\n",
    "\n",
    "LDA is a probabilistic model that assumes each document is a mixture of topics and each topic is a distribution of words. It performs well in identifying general themes in large text corpora. However, LDA relies heavily on word frequency and does not capture semantic meaning effectively. As a result, the generated topics may sometimes include unrelated words, leading to lower interpretability and coherence compared to more advanced models.\n",
    "2. LSA (Latent Semantic Analysis)\n",
    "\n",
    "LSA uses matrix decomposition (SVD) to identify latent relationships between words and documents. It is effective in capturing hidden structures in text data. However, similar to LDA, LSA does not fully capture contextual meaning. The topics generated by LSA are often harder to interpret because they are based on linear algebra transformations rather than probabilistic distributions.\n",
    "3. BERTopic\n",
    "\n",
    "BERTopic is a modern topic modeling technique that leverages transformer-based embeddings and clustering algorithms. It captures semantic relationships between words and documents much more effectively than LDA and LSA. As a result, BERTopic produces more coherent and meaningful topics. Additionally, it provides better visualization tools, making it easier to interpret and analyze the topics.\n",
    "4. Modified BERTopic\n",
    "\n",
    "The modified BERTopic model further improves upon the default version by allowing customization of embedding models and clustering algorithms (e.g., using Sentence-Transformers and DBSCAN). This flexibility can lead to improved performance depending on the dataset. In some cases, it may produce more refined or domain-specific topics. However, it requires careful tuning of parameters, and improper settings may lead to less stable or lower-quality topics.\n",
    "Final Comparison and Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Among all four models, BERTopic and Modified BERTopic perform the best, as they utilize advanced embedding techniques that capture semantic meaning rather than relying solely on word frequency.\n",
    "\n",
    "Best Overall: BERTopic\n",
    "Most Flexible: Modified BERTopic\n",
    "Moderate Performance: LDA\n",
    "Lowest Interpretability: LSA\n",
    "\n",
    "BERTopic generally provides the highest coherence scores and the most interpretable topics because it uses contextual embeddings. The modified version can outperform the default model when properly tuned, but it may also introduce variability.\n",
    "Final Comparison and Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Among all four models, BERTopic and Modified BERTopic perform the best, as they utilize advanced embedding techniques that capture semantic meaning rather than relying solely on word frequency.\n",
    "\n",
    "Best Overall: BERTopic\n",
    "Most Flexible: Modified BERTopic\n",
    "Moderate Performance: LDA\n",
    "Lowest Interpretability: LSA\n",
    "\n",
    "BERTopic generally provides the highest coherence scores and the most interpretable topics because it uses contextual embeddings. The modified version can outperform the default model when properly tuned, but it may also introduce variability."
   ]
